---
// "Three panes": uses the real dux screenshot (assets/dux-screenshot.svg,
// copied into public/ at build time) instead of a CSS approximation.
---

<section class="anchor-offset py-16 sm:py-24">
  <div class="container-app">
    <div class="max-w-2xl">
      <span class="pill">▸ the office tour</span>
      <h2 class="heading mt-3 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">
        Three panes. <span class="text-[color:var(--color-accent)]">Unlimited</span> agents.
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-[color:var(--color-muted)] leading-relaxed">
        Most AI coding tools give you one agent in one directory. dux gives you unlimited agents across unlimited worktrees, all visible at once. Spawn five agents on five branches and let them work in parallel.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-8 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-3">
      <div class="card p-4">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
          <span class="flex h-5 w-5 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-md bg-[color:var(--color-accent)]/15 text-[color:var(--color-accent)] mono text-[11px]">1</span>
          <strong class="text-sm text-[color:var(--color-text)]">Left</strong>
        </div>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-[color:var(--color-muted)]">Your projects and agent sessions, plus the companion terminals list. Click. Switch. Sorted.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card p-4">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
          <span class="flex h-5 w-5 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-md bg-[color:var(--color-accent)]/15 text-[color:var(--color-accent)] mono text-[11px]">2</span>
          <strong class="text-sm text-[color:var(--color-text)]">Center</strong>
        </div>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-[color:var(--color-muted)]">The agent's live terminal: full PTY, full output, the same CLI you'd run by hand.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card p-4">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
          <span class="flex h-5 w-5 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-md bg-[color:var(--color-accent)]/15 text-[color:var(--color-accent)] mono text-[11px]">3</span>
          <strong class="text-sm text-[color:var(--color-text)]">Right</strong>
        </div>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-[color:var(--color-muted)]">Staged files, syntax-highlighted diffs, AI commit messages. The full git dance, toggleable away when you want room.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <figure class="mt-10">
      <div
        class="overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-[color:var(--color-border)]"
        style="box-shadow: 0 0 0 1px color-mix(in oklab, var(--color-accent) 8%, transparent), 0 30px 80px -30px color-mix(in oklab, var(--color-accent) 30%, transparent), 0 50px 140px -50px color-mix(in oklab, var(--color-pink) 22%, transparent);"
      >
        <img
          src="/dux-screenshot.svg"
          alt="dux running: a projects pane with a tree of agent sessions on the left, a Claude agent's live terminal in the center, and the dux header bar showing project, branch, agent, and provider."
          width="1609"
          height="784"
          loading="lazy"
          class="block w-full bg-[color:var(--color-ink)]"
        />
      </div>
      <figcaption class="mt-3 text-center mono text-[11px] text-[color:var(--color-dim)]">
        actual dux · not a mockup · Tab between panes · resize with keys or mouse · go fullscreen with interactive mode
      </figcaption>
    </figure>
  </div>
</section>
